–1190":"1121–1190","1135–1212":"1135–1212","1170–1228":"1170–1228","1165–Male":"1165–Afdød","–1168":"–1168","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","about 1170":"omkring 1170","1168":"1168","1212":"1212","1135":"1135","1121":"1121","31 August 1168":"31. august 1168","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Skotland","Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England":"Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England","Durazzo Greece":"Durrës, Durrës, Albanien"},"nl":{"1121–1190":"1121–1190","1135–1212":"1135–1212","1170–1228":"1170–1228","1165–Male":"1165–Overleden","–1168":"–1168","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","about 1170":"circa 1170","1168":"1168","1212":"1212","1135":"1135","1121":"1121","31 August 1168":"31 augustus 1168","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Schotland","Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England":"Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England","Durazzo Greece":"Durrës, Durrës, Albanië"},"en":{"1121–1190":"1121–1190","1135–1212":"1135–1212","1170–1228":"1170–1228","1165–Male":"1165–Deceased","–1168":"–1168","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","about 1170":"about 1170","1168":"1168","1212":"1212","1135":"1135","1121":"1121","31 August 1168":"31 August 1168","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England":"Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England","Durazzo Greece":"Durrës, Durrës, Albania","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Beaumont","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Gilles, Gaetan, Honore, Jacques, Jean-Guy, Marcel.","English (of Norman origin) and French: habitational name from any of the five places in Normandy or several others elsewhere in France so named. The placename comes from Old French <i>beu</i>, <i>bel</i> ‘fair, lovely’ + <i>mont</i> ‘hill’. There are also places in England so named under Norman influence in Cumberland, Lancashire, and Essex, the last of which changed its name in the 12th century from <i>Fulepet</i> ‘foul pit’ to <i>Bealmont</i> ‘beautiful hill’; these may also have given rise to the surname. The surname is now widespread throughout England, but most common in Yorkshire. Compare   Belmont  .","History: Many English bearers of this surname are descended from Henry de Beaumont (died 1340), who came to England from France as a soldier, serving Kings Edward I, II, and III of England. He acquired the earldom of Buchan in Scotland by marriage. — Many American bearers of this surname are descendants of John Beaumont (1612–47), who came to North America from England in 1630. William Beaumont came from England to Cambridge MA in 1635 and subsequently moved to CT."],"variants":[{"name":"Bement","meanings":["English (Cambridgeshire): variant of   Beaumont  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Beeman","meanings":["English (Kent): occupational name for a beekeeper, from Middle English <i>bee-man</i> ‘bee-keeper’ (Old English <i>bēo</i> + <i>mann</i>).","English (Kent): variant of   Beaumont  .","Americanized form of German   Biemann   or of its Dutch cognate <b>Bieman</b>."]},{"name":"Belmont","meanings":["French and English (of Norman origin): variant of   Beaumont  .","Catalan: habitational name from the placename Bellmont ‘beautiful mountain’. Compare Spanish   Belmonte  ."]},{"name":"Baumunk","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Siegmund.","German: probably a Germanized form of a French Huguenot name <b>Beaumont</b> (see also   Beaumont  )."]},{"name":"Bayman","meanings":["English (mainly Lancashire): variant of   Beaumont  .","Americanized form of German <b>Beumann</b> or <b>Bäumann</b>, variants of   Baumann  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"III","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Japanese Yuko, Aiko, Hideaki, Hiroki, Hiroyuki, Isamu, Kaoru, Katsumi, Keiichiro, Kenji, Masako, Masayuki.","Japanese: variously written, sometimes with characters used phonetically; the most probable meanings are 仁井 ‘benevolent well’, 新居 ‘new residence’, or 新井 ‘new well’. It is not common in Japan."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Third Earl Leicester Robert III de Beaumont was born in 1121 as the son of Richard and Amice De Gael Heiress Of Breteuil. He had at least 1 son with Petronella de Grandmesnil. He died in 1190, in Durrës, Durrës, Albania, at the age of 69."},"et":{"1121–1190":"1121–1190","1135–1212":"1135–1212","1170–1228":"1170–1228","1165–Male":"1165–Surnud","–1168":"–1168","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1168":"1168","1212":"1212","1135":"1135","1121":"1121","31 August 1168":"31. august 1168","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England":"Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England","Durazzo Greece":"Durrës, Durrës, Albaania"},"fi":{"1121–1190":"1121–1190","1135–1212":"1135–1212","1170–1228":"1170–1228","1165–Male":"1165–Kuollut","–1168":"–1168","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","about 1170":"noin 1170","1168":"1168","1212":"1212","1135":"1135","1121":"1121","31 August 1168":"31. elokuuta 1168","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England":"Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England","Durazzo Greece":"Durrës, Durrës, Albania"},"fr":{"1121–1190":"1121–1190","1135–1212":"1135–1212","1170–1228":"1170–1228","1165–Male":"1165–Décédé","–1168":"–1168","1190":"1190","1228":"1228","about 1170":"environ 1170","1168":"1168","1212":"1212","1135":"1135","1121":"1121","31 August 1168":"31 août 1168","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Blackhall, Renfrewshire, Écosse","Nuneaton, Warwickshire, England":"Nuneaton, Warwickshire, Angleterre","Durazzo Greece":"Durrës, Durrës, Albanie","lifeSummary":"Third Earl Leicester Robert III de Beaumont est né en 1121, fils de Richard et Amice De Gael Heiress Of Breteuil. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Petronella de Grandmesnil. Il est décédé en 1190, à Durrës, Durrës, Albanie, à l’âge de 69 ans."},"de":{"1121–1190":"1121–1190","1135–1212":"1135–1212","1170–1228":"1170–1228","1165–Male":"1165–Verstorben","–1168":"–1168","1190